# Massive API Data Source Rule

Agents must use Massive API for market data in this repository.

- Use Massive REST or flat-file data for equities, crypto, options, indices,
  forex, and futures data whenever a notebook, script, analysis, or helper needs
  historical or live market prices, trades, quotes, aggregates, snapshots, or
  reference data.
- Do not introduce new Yahoo Finance, yfinance, pandas-datareader, Stooq,
  Alpha Vantage, Nasdaq Data Link, exchange-specific public scrape, or other
  third-party market data fetches unless the user explicitly requests that
  provider for the task.
- Read the Massive API key from environment/configuration, preferably
  `MASSIVE_API_KEY` or an ignored local `.env` file. Never hard-code API keys or
  commit credentials.
- When aligning prices across instruments or asset classes, prefer Massive
  timestamped aggregate bars at the finest practical granularity for the
  research question, then document the timestamp convention and alignment rule
  in the notebook or helper.
- If Massive cannot provide the required dataset or the environment is missing
  credentials, fail clearly with an actionable message instead of silently
  falling back to another provider.
